6. Note on tlee Similes.

Vergil has followed Homer in beautifying his poem with a great many comparisons, many of them indeed directly borrowed from the lliad or other Greek sources. Once we have an original simile of a strikingly Roman quality, where Neptune stilling the storm is compared to a great and good man whose simple presence quiets a tumult (i. 148).
